# NEB test example for GPUMD
# This example demonstrates the NEB (Nudged Elastic Band) method
# for finding transition states and minimum energy paths

# Load the potential
potential nep89.txt

# Run NEB calculation
# Syntax: neb <nreplica> <etol> <ftol> <n1steps> <n2steps> <nevery> [keywords]
#   nreplica: number of replicas (images) along the path (minimum 3)
#   etol: energy tolerance for convergence (eV)
#   ftol: force tolerance for convergence (eV/Angstrom)
#   n1steps: maximum steps for regular NEB stage
#   n2steps: maximum steps for climbing NEB stage (0 to skip)
#   nevery: output frequency
# Optional keywords:
#   spring <value>: spring constant (default 1.0 eV/Angstrom^2)
#   final <filename>: final configuration file (required)
#   free_end_ini: free end for initial replica
#   free_end_final: free end for final replica
#   mode <neighbor|ideal|equal>: NEB mode

neb 7 1.0e-6 1.0e-4 1000 1000 10 final final.xyz spring 5.0
